<br>
It be having tha same chance to land, slightly better since it lacks damage check, than QWoT.<br>
<br>
Ah repeat... REMOVE tha stun effect and make it a strong knockback effect. Like 10-15 units. That will interrupt any caster.<br>
<br>
No complicated stun immune/level issues. Anything can be moved by knockback that dunnae be rooted in place. Ah propose this for Thunder o Karana moreso than this skill but tha same problem has tha same simple answer.<br>
<br>
Ah want it to land vs decent resistance too, like 100 magic resist. Ya have to be concerned on yer knockback direction too. Adds come risk to tha ability.<br>
<br>
Ano'er idea... for Divine Stun make it MULTIPLY tha knockback effect of existing paladin stuns. Those be Force, QWoT, and... ah propose ToK as a mana seive DD (-120), debuff (magic-20), knockback (6) with 4 tick duration and 10 tick recast.<br>
<br>
Divine Stun 3/6/9 Multiples knockback effect on paladin's high level stun spells to improve their chances to interrupt anything. Tha multipliers be 1.5, 2, 3 times tha knockback.<br>
<br>
This would give oor top end stun QWoT a knockback of 15=(5)*3 which matches such powers as Wizard 29 - Thunderstrike and 39 - Thunderclap.<br>
